marc21:datafield.marc21:subfield: Title based in part on handwritten title page which reads: A trip abroad; vol. I; journal of Gertrude Vanderbilt; May, 1890; from New York to London to Paris to London to New York to Newport. <br>Whitney documents her boat voyage across the Atlantic and back; sightseeing in London and Paris; lessons in painting and other subjects, horseback riding and social events in Newport. <br>Several newspaper clippings documenting Vanderbilt society parties are enclosed. <br>Some entries are written in French. <br>Any citation of this collection must include the following title designated by the donor: Whitney Museum of American Art, Gertrude Vanderbilt Whitney papers. Gift of Flora Miller Irving.
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
